abstract: New York Jets Coach Rex Ryan holds news conference to discuss his concerns after team's loss to Baltimore Ravens; says team abandoned its running game and failed to protect quarterback Mark Sanchez, two entwined notions that he vows will change.
snippet: The Jets thought they had a few things figured out after losing to the Raiders, but then came Sunday’s loss to the Ravens.
lead_paragraph: The Jets thought they had a few things figured out after losing to the Raiders, but then came Sunday’s loss to the Ravens.

headline.main: Losses Turn Up Heat Under Ryan’s Collar
